Hunters Valley Busing is seeking safe, reliable individuals to become School Bus Route and/or Sports Drivers for Greenwood School District. We cover all fees for training, licensing and clearances with our in-house instruction team for all qualified candidates. Our company pays weekly, offers competitive wages with monthly attendance bonuses and runs a well-maintained bus fleet. School bus driving is a perfect opportunity for stay at home parents and newly retired folks to make some extra cash! Email: huntersvalley@embarqmail.com Call: (717)215-3017

There will be a free produce distribution at the Millerstown Community Park Tuesday, September 15th at 3:30 pm.

This distribution is sponsored by the SKIP program (USDA & Farm to Fork outreach) and there is no income restrictions.

Thousands of boxes of vegetables to give away.
It is a drive through...so please stay in your vehicle.

If successful, they would like to schedule a monthly distribution.

post_text: Be The Light! In honor of the Class of 2020, first responders, healthcare workers, and all who are on the front line of dealing with the COVID-19 pandemic.
text: Be The Light! In honor of the Class of 2020, first responders, healthcare workers, and all who are on the front line of dealing with the COVID-19 pandemic.

post_text:
Greenwood will be participating in the National “Be the Light” campaign tomorrow, 4/17 at Dar Roush Memorial Field. This campaign is to honor the graduating class of 2020, and first responders, healthcare workers, and all who are on the front line of dealing with the COVID-19 pandemic. Please note supporters are NOT to travel to the field tomorrow evening. Pictures will be shared on social media and the Greenwood School District website. The lights will be turned on for 20 minutes at 8:20pm (20:20 military time) and the scoreboard will read time of 20:20.

We cannot stress this enough, supporters of this initiative should not be on Greenwood School District property.
